result.execSummary:
All charges against Takeya Marie Calvin-Swope in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Takeya Marie Calvin-Swope is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Attorney Thomas Evangelos Harris in court by video, defendant Takeya Marie Calvin-Swope not in court, in custody.  Edward OBrien appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a preliminary hearing. States witness is not present. Defense moves to dismiss; motion is granted. Case is dismissed without prejudice.

Defendant Takeya Marie Calvin-Swope in court with attorney Thomas Evangelos Harris.  Defendant Takeya Marie Calvin-Swope in custody.  Adam Joseph Best appeared for the State of Wisconsin. PARTIES APPEAR BY VIDEO.  
Case in court for Preliminary Hearing. State's witness is unavailable. State requests an adjournment. Defense move to dismiss. Court denies defense's motion and ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility. Defense request to be heard as to bail on the next court date.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 1, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Takeya Marie Calvin-Swope in court with attorney Thomas Evangelos Harris.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case called in Branch 25 with defendant's cases 21CF1871 & 21CF754. 
Court finds good cause to appoint Tom Harris as counsel at county expense.  Attorney Harris to be paid at $125.00 and defendant is not required to repay the county due to indigency.   Court ordered case adjourned for bail bond hearing/status conference in Branch 25.  Bail/bond hearing scheduled for July 12, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Court ordered no contact with McDonald's; DS
No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Takeya Marie Calvin-Swope in court with attorney Stephen Andrew Sargent.  Defendant Takeya Marie Calvin-Swope in custody.  Abby Rockendorf appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Takeya Marie Calvin-Swope appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Sanders, Branch 28.  Per Chief Judge Directive 22-04 effective June 13, 2022, this calendar will be assigned to Reserve Judge John Franke, in Room 608 of the Courthouse. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  Defense enters a plea of NOT GUILTY as to misdemeanor count 2.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 17, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
